43298]},{"section":5,"text":"Alkaline phosphatase is usually elevated in issues with the bile ducts or bone, but since he's presenting with jaundice, it's more likely related to the liver or bile ducts.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.055183,0.068101,0.087148,0.1003,0.10423,0.10394,0.10472,0.093855,0.084937,0.077764,0.064942,0.05488],"unified_progress":[0.050887,0.073216,0.088398,0.097441,0.10077,0.10195,0.10087,0.094802,0.08832,0.081572,0.068624,0.053154]},{"section":6,"text":"The transaminases being only minimally increased suggests that the problem isn't as severe in the liver itself but more in the bile ducts.","dimension":7,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046852,0.05849,0.079422,0.091662,0.099058,0.10207,0.10332,0.098159,0.092219,0.085958,0.077231,0.065567],"unified_progress":[0.044909,0.065625,0.081005,0.090077,0.097206,0.098278,0.098907,0.097376,0.0948,0.0899,0.078713,0.063204]},{"section":7,"text":"He was referred to a surgeon, which makes me think it's something that might require surgical intervention.","dimension":0,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045185,0.081885,0.089276,0.092536,0.090788,0.090887,0.094031,0.091047,0.088388,0.091753,0.079358,0.064866],"unified_progress":[0.057336,0.086959,0.087433,0.091246,0.091791,0.091432,0.092233,0.092902,0.088587,0.085892,0.07433,0.059857]},{"section":8,"text":"The endoscopic retrograde cholangiography (ERCP) findings are key here: multiple strictures and saccular dilatations in both intrahepatic and extrahepatic bile ducts.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024768,0.05918,0.087906,0.11695,0.11818,0.12057,0.11817,0.10593,0.084726,0.066299,0.054572,0.042744],"unified_progress":[0.032281,0.072742,0.093976,0.11119,0.11234,0.1049,0.1005,0.091459,0.10177,0.070786,0.057829,0.050229]},{"section":9,"text":"ERCP is used to visualize the bile ducts, so seeing these changes points towards a cholangiopathy.","dimension":1,